        <updateDate>2021-08-20T01:26:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>USA FREEDOM Reauthorization Act of 2020</strong></p> <p>This bill modifies provisions related to foreign intelligence surveillance. Among other things, the bill (1) repeals authorities providing for ongoing access to call detail records; (2) requires the Office of the Director of National Intelligence to decide whether to declassify a significant Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court decision within 180 days of the decision; and (3) requires government officers to disclose all relevant information, including any exculpatory information, when applying for a court order under certain foreign surveillance authorities.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
